    "These approaches have already shown promising results and could reduce the burden on pathologists in today's medical landscape 10.",
    "A major drawback of current methods is that they are typically limited to a narrow task, providing only a single scalar output for each input.",
    "Consider, for example, an image classification model for benign versus malignant tissue.",
    "Beyond predicting these two labels, the model cannot do anything else: neither solve new unseen problems (called zero-shot prediction) nor provide its reasoning steps for better explainability.",
    "Vision language foundation models offer an exciting alternative to these rigid approaches by processing both images and text simultaneously."
